# Linux File Compression & Archiving

## Tools Covered

- tar
- gzip
- zip
- unzip

---

## Purpose

- Backups
- File transfer
- Storage optimization

---

## Common Commands

```bash
tar -cvf
tar -tvf
tar -xvf
gzip
gunzip
zip
unzip
```

---

## Key Takeaways

- tar archives files.
- gzip compresses files.
- zip archives and compresses.
- .tar.gz is widely used for Linux backups.
